* BMAP CRSM (create-symbol) macro mode: with CRSM ON, a macro reference beyond
* the supplied args (#9 here) expands to a generated unique label _NNNN_, so a
* macro that defines a local label can be called repeatedly without colliding.
* GENJ is called twice -> _0000_ / _0001_ (distinct), each TRA #9 referencing
* its own.  #1 is the ordinary argument (5, then 6).
       OUNAME CRSMT
       CRSM   ON
GENJ   MACRO
#9     EQU    *
       TRA    #9
       LDA    #1
       ENDM
       GENJ   5
       GENJ   6
       END
